.Dd May 27, 2026
.Dt KILONODE-COMPAT 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm kilonode-compat
.Nd replay KiloNode compatibility lab transcripts
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm check-transcript
.Ar path
.Nm
.Cm replay-transcript
.Ar path
.Nm
.Cm replay-dir
.Ar path
.Nm
.Cm report-transcript
.Ar path
.Nm
.Cm check-observation
.Ar path
.Nm
.Cm show-observation
.Ar path
.Nm
.Cm observe-process
.Fl -binary Ar path
.Fl -config Ar path
.Fl -name Ar name
.Fl -mode Ar mode
.Fl -input Ar text
.Fl -output Ar path
.Op Fl -timeout Ar seconds
.Nm
.Cm observe-tcp
.Fl -host Ar host
.Fl -port Ar port
.Fl -name Ar name
.Fl -mode Ar mode
.Fl -input Ar text
.Fl -output Ar path
.Op Fl -timeout Ar seconds
.Nm
.Cm make-transcript-from-observation
.Ar path
.Fl -output Ar path
.Nm
.Cm compare-observations
.Ar left
.Ar right
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
validates and replays KiloNode-native compatibility transcripts.
The current replay mode is synthetic RF UI command ingress. It can also validate
and store black-box observation files.
.Pp
The tool does not run LinBPQ, inspect GPL source, open real transports, or
dispatch queued transmit frames unless the operator explicitly requests a
bounded observation command.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -help
Show command usage.
.El
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm check-transcript Ar path
Validate transcript syntax.
.It Cm replay-transcript Ar path
Replay one transcript and print a text report.
.It Cm replay-dir Ar path
Replay all
.Pa *.transcript
files in sorted order.
.It Cm report-transcript Ar path
Print the parsed transcript fields without replay.
.It Cm check-observation Ar path
Validate one black-box observation file.
.It Cm show-observation Ar path
Print sanitized observation metadata and a bounded output preview.
.It Cm observe-process
Run an explicitly supplied binary with bounded stdout and stderr capture.
.It Cm observe-tcp
Connect to an explicitly supplied TCP endpoint, send one bounded line, and
capture a bounded response.
.It Cm make-transcript-from-observation Ar path Fl -output Ar path
Write a transcript candidate marked as black-box observation data.
.It Cm compare-observations Ar left Ar right
Compare two observations at text level.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa tests/fixtures/compat
Synthetic KiloNode-native baseline fixtures.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal
kilonode-compat check-transcript tests/fixtures/compat/rf-ping.transcript
kilonode-compat replay-dir tests/fixtures/compat
kilonode-compat check-observation tests/fixtures/compat/blackbox-node-help.observation
kilonode-compat show-observation tests/fixtures/compat/blackbox-node-help.observation
.Ed
.Sh SECURITY NOTES
Treat transcript files as hostile input.
Synthetic replay never dispatches TX frames.
Future LinBPQ observations must be black-box behaviour only.
LinBPQ is not run automatically; process observation requires an explicit
binary path from the operator.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kilonodectl 1 ,
.Xr kilonoded 8
